The paper deals with the verification of multi-agent systems (MAS) with resource bounds, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of temporal logic and game theory suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. The focus on coalitional games and the modeling of real-world scenarios involving resource availability and pricing suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
